Distribution represents a frequency distribution of double-valued
sample points. It contains the size of the population of sample
points plus additional optional information:

-  the arithmetic mean of the samples
-  the minimum and maximum of the samples
-  the sum-squared-deviation of the samples, used to compute
   variance
-  a histogram of the values of the sample points

members.

        The total number of samples in the

        The arithmetic mean of the samples in the distribution. If

        The minimum of the population of values. Ignored if

count.description: The total number of samples in the distribution. Must be >= 0.

mean.description: The arithmetic mean of the samples in the distribution. If ``count`` is zero then this field must be zero.

The buckets are defined below in ``bucket_option``. exemplars.description: Example points. Must be in increasing order of ``value`` field.
